in 2018 i bought podcasting equipment because i had an idea of starting a podcast. in 2019 i did some research on them. in 2020 i told myself it was too hard to start so i tried an easier route and made it an IGTV series instead. in 2021 I was still thinking about the dream i had in 2018. it was time to decide ‘one day’ or ‘day one.’ and so i wrote my first 5 episodes and recorded them all in one sitting.

if you know me, you know my biggest piece of advice is “confidence is a byproduct of action: you don’t get confident then take action, you take action and then you get confident.” it took 3 years of procrastinating to realize i needed to take my own advice. and now only a year & a half later with 82 episodes under my belt, taking that messy action has led to my first million downloads. let this inspire you that if it were impossible, you would’ve never had the vision. believe in your vision & trust in yourself🤍 

thank you to every single person who’s ever listened, downloaded, shared + reposted, left a review, subscribed, followed my accounts, commented + liked pictures, told a friend or now bought the crewneck! every ounce of support matters just as much🫶🏻

last night I found photos of my late grandpa in the war that he sent to my late grandma while she waited for him with love letters on the back of each one. it reminded me the importance of my favorite Bible verse 1 Corinthians 13: 4-8, “love is patient.”

I’ve spent 10 years praying for my husband. many people don’t understand how someone is 28 without having many long term relationships, as if they are seen as accolades. but what they don’t know is that I pray to God about every guy I’ve ever dated (even if it was literally one date) asking “if he’s not for me, please remove him.” his answer reveals itself through: insecurity, confusion, incompatibility, bad communication, disappointment, lack of chemistry, doubt, unattractiveness, etc. they say when you know, you know, & I can confirm when you don’t know, you know, too. so i’ve always said one of the most important qualities I need in a husband is patience because I’ve never been loved properly. some say I’m crazy for not giving more guys a chance or for ending things so quickly with the guys I gave chances to, but I say those people don’t truly see me or understand my soul. I’m certain that my husband will admire that I’ve saved myself for him in so many ways. I’m certain he will feel blessed to know that no man has ever had the version of me he will have🤍

slides 1-2: a photo he sent & some of my favorite love letters on the back 
slide 3-5: a prayer about patience I wrote in September 2022
slide 6: one of my fav stories of patience, love & faith. in a dream, she asks God to pick for her. He said “if you really want me to pick with you, then I will custom make it for you. but here’s the thing about custom made pieces: they take longer, & it’s gonna mean you’re empty handed for a bit.” 
slide 7: todays episode of FTG with a story of patience, love, & faith by @lfgbabe. how she went from toxic relationships, to healing & then going from single to engaged in 3 months + married in 7 months. 
slide 8: my Corinthians tattoo I got 10 years ago on my parents 25 year wedding anniversary back in 2013
slide 9: the verse written out🫶🏻

INTRODUCING THE CONFIDENCE CLUB🍸// SWIPE ➡️ // for the girls who want to grow at their own pace, at an affordable rate. my most inclusive coaching program yet is here & my heart couldn’t be happier. 

if you want daily coaching without a time commitment, or a start & end date, or a 4 figure monthly investment — the confidence club is for you. 

this is something I’ve been considering doing for over a year — but sometimes it’s hard for an entrepreneur to drop their ego and offer something so high value at such a low ticket price. yet why was it still weighing on me so much? because I’m driven by making an impact, building a community, and opening the hearts & minds of others. something will always be missing if I’m not serving as many people as I feel called to do, and I only feel connected to my work when it’s aligned with my souls purpose. im a naturally gifted healer & i am so grateful to be able to share my gift with the world on social media. 

making a difference and creating the space for the emotional healing of others is what I was born to do. after 2 years of offering 1:1 coaching, I’ve completely reworked my programs into 3 tiers this past week, and I couldn’t be more excited to offer the confidence club as an opportunity to make that space for so many more of you. for all the details, head to victoriaalario.com🤍✨
the confidence club is live now at victoriaalario.com🍸

one of the most special moments this year was showering @alexandrarosemunch. to say I am proud of you would be an understatement — I’m a combination of all different feelings & emotions as I reflect on your journey over the past few years. I’ve been protective of you as a crazy college girl, have loved having you as my go to dinner date, have understood you even when you didn’t understand yourself, and am now in awe of you as a momma to be who’s devoted to her faith. every couple of weeks we text each other in shock of how our year has started & how it’s ending, and I’m still in disbelief of how much we’ve grown & evolved while our worlds have changed around us this year. but through it all one things for certain, I’m so blessed to have you in my life and to be a part of yours. our friendship is so special to me, you’re my best friend and I am so excited for what’s to come with y(our) baby. ♾️

vision board goal accomplished: for the girls is officially signed to the podcast nation roster✨ 

being signed to a podcast network has been my dream since @forthegirls.podcast came to life in august of 2021. for the past two years, I’ve been an independent podcaster with a mission to turn this passion project into my career. it’s been on my vision board since 2021 & i didn’t care how long it took. this was always going to be a matter of ‘when,’ NOT a matter of ‘if.’ my WHY has always been & will always be to help women become more confident, boost their self love, & embody their unapologetic selves, and my podcast has been the greatest outlet to do exactly that. 

I’ve believed in myself, had an amazing community believing in me, & just needed a team to believe in me, too. i was never afraid of dealing with rejection, because I know if you’re being told ‘no’ you’re just asking the wrong person. and so as it was meant to be, I found @podcast.nation (exactly when & how I was supposed to) & they were the right team to believe in me and my show. 

i am so unbelievably excited to grow for the girls, represent podcast nation, and create bigger and better content for my community. new guests, new ideas, new topics, all coming soon. if you’ve been here, i’m so grateful for you. if you’re new here, i’m so happy to welcome you. thank you all for supporting my dreams coming true🫶🏻
